## Summary

clawq already has detection for several flavors of broken agent
behavior — but the detector is observe-only. It logs and moves on.
Today's daemon.log has 50+ stuck-detected WARNs, 7 distinct
stuck-reason patterns on postmortems, ~118 consecutive empty-arg
tool calls on the teams session, and a postmortem currently burning
$5/session on a repeating grep — all of these landed in the log,
none of them stopped.

What exists today:

- `[observer] stuck detected ...` (src/observer*.ml): detects 'SameErrorString',
  'message-count stuck' patterns; emits WARN
- Postmortem circuit breaker (B395): suppresses postmortem RE-launch on
  same pattern; does not pause the main loop
- Mutex deadlock watchdog (B643 scope): 610s hard-kill on session lock,
  aborts daemon — too aggressive AND too late
- Cron consecutive-identical-output detection (B632, done): pauses cron
  jobs — but only cron jobs

Missing: a single 'agent health watchdog' that acts on:

1. N consecutive identical tool errors / empty-args / SameErrorString
   (B634/B639 territory)
2. N consecutive identical responses without tool calls (B650 territory,
   already detected on postmortems but no action)
3. Cost burn rate: per-session cost crosses a configurable threshold
   (e.g., \$2/hour, \$10/session) without user-visible progress
4. Cycle detection: same (tool_name, args_hash) appearing M times in
   the last N turns (B649 reproduced this — same background_task_wait
   call 3 times)

Common action surface, regardless of detector:

- Pause the session (no new turns, no new dispatch) until user input
- Post a one-line summary to the user channel: 'I appear stuck on
  <pattern>. Last useful turn: <ts>. Pausing.'
- Roll back to the last good checkpoint OR leave history intact
  (configurable; default: leave intact, user decides)
- Optionally cancel in-flight provider calls / background tasks
- Emit a structured event so dashboards can count incidents

## Suggested fix

1. Factor the existing observer detectors into a single
   `Agent_health.evaluate ~session_key ~history -> health_status`
   returning `Healthy | Suspect of reason | Stuck of reason`.
2. Add an action plane: `Agent_health.on_stuck session reason` that
   does the pause + user-notify + structured-event work.
3. Hook into the per-turn agent loop (`src/agent.ml`) immediately
   after each turn. Cheap call, runs once per turn.
4. Make thresholds configurable in `runtime_config.t`:
   `stuck_consecutive_identical_errors : int` (default 3),
   `stuck_consecutive_no_progress : int` (default 5),
   `stuck_session_cost_ceiling_usd : float option` (default None).

## Relationship to existing bugs

- B395 (done): postmortem circuit breaker → narrower kill-switch
- B632 (done): cron consecutive-identical detection → similar shape
- B639 (open): main loop stuck escalation → subset of this
- B643 (open): mutex deadlock auto-abort → too-late safety net
- B650 (open): postmortem self-stuck → would be caught by this

This bug supersedes (or umbrellas) B639 and B650 — they are the
detector half; this is the action half.

## Evidence

- ~/.clawq/daemon.log: 50+ stuck-detected WARNs in single session
- Live right now (00:25): postmortem session 1779372943 has done 4
  identical greps over 20s at \$4.98 session cost, still going